Java program to swap two numbers using bitwise operator

[Java program to swap two numbers using bitwise operator](https://www.flowerbrackets.com/java-program-to-swap-two-numbers-using-bitwise-operator/)

Bitwise xor operator compares bits of two operands. If two operands are equal it returns 1 else 0 if they are not equal. Here’s the program to swap two numbers using 
bitwise xor operator.

import java.util.Scanner;
public class SwapUsingBitwiseDemo 
{
   public static void main(String[] args) 
   {
      int a, b;
      Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
      System.out.println("First number : ");
      a = sc.nextInt();
      System.out.println("Second number : ");
      b = sc.nextInt();
      // xor operator java
      a = a ^ b;
      b = a ^ b;
      a = a ^ b;
      // swapping numbers in java
      System.out.println("After Swapping - ");
      System.out.println("First number : " + a);
      System.out.println("Second number : " + b);
      sc.close();
   }
}


Output:

First number : 50
Second number : 100
After Swapping –
First number : 100
Second number : 50
